\begin{definition*}[Opposite category]
  {}
  Given a category~\CatC, the \emph{\iindex{opposite category}}~$\CatC\op$ has the same objects as~\CatC, but a morphism~$\mora\colon \Obja\to \Objb$ in~$\CatC\op$ is the same as a morphism~$\mora\colon \Objb\to \Obja$ in~\CatC. Furthermore, a composite of morphisms~$\mora \mthen \morb$ in~$\CatC\op$ is the composite~$\morb\then \mora$ in~\CatC.\end{definition*}
